2
00:02:35,300 --> 00:02:39,500
あー、あー、あー！皆様、おー！
Ah, ah, ah! Hello, everyone!

3
00:02:39,900 --> 00:02:42,500
いいですね！コメント元気だね！
Nice! The comments are so lively!

4
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:48,300
本日は風真いろは生誕ライブ2026「Wind Trails」に
Today, thank you so much for coming...

5
00:02:48,300 --> 00:02:51,500
ご来場くださいまして、誠にありがとうございます！
...to Kazama Iroha Birthday Live 2026 "Wind Trails"!

6
00:02:51,500 --> 00:02:53,000
いえーい！
Yay!

7
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:58,300
開演に先立ちまして、皆様にお願いとご案内を申し上げます。
Prior to the show starting, I have a few requests and notices.

8
00:02:58,500 --> 00:03:01,800
開演中、カメラやスマートフォンなどは、
During the performance, regarding cameras and smartphones...

9
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:04,500
電源を切られると見れなくなって困るので、
If you turn them off, you won't be able to watch, which would suck,

10
00:03:04,500 --> 00:03:07,800
電源は切らず、写真撮影などね、大量にしていただき、
so don't turn them off! Take lots of photos,

11
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:13,000
当配信のハッシュタグ「風真いろは生誕ライブ2026」で、
and post tons of pictures on social media with the hashtag...

12
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:16,200
SNSに大量に画像ポストしてください！
...#風真いろは生誕ライブ2026!

13
00:03:16,500 --> 00:03:19,300
目指せ！Xトレンド1位！
Let's aim for the number one trending spot on X!

14
00:03:19,300 --> 00:03:22,500
よろしくお願いいたします！
Thank you for your support!

15
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:27,500
あ、あの、でもスマホね、いっぱい写真撮ったりすると充電なくなっちゃいそうなんで、
Oh, but taking tons of photos on your phone might drain your battery,

16
00:03:27,500 --> 00:03:31,500
スマホで見てる勢は、えー、充電しっかりしてくださいね！
so if you're watching on your phone, please make sure it's fully charged!

17
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:34,800
はい、そしてその2！
Alright, number two!

18
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:40,500
激しく頭を振る、えー、激しくペンライトを振る、などはですね、
Shaking your head or waving your penlight too violently...

19
00:03:40,500 --> 00:03:45,000
あなた様の、ご自宅を破壊する危険性がございますので、
...carries the risk of destroying your home.

20
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:49,000
破壊されてもですね、こちらでは責任一切負えませんので、
We cannot take any responsibility if your room gets wrecked,

21
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:51,500
お気をつけください！だめだよ、みんな！
so please be careful! No breaking things, okay?

22
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:54,000
あ、そしてあと、もう1個、その3！
Oh, and one more thing, number three!

23
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:59,000
今からハヤシライスを準備しようとしてるやつは、間に合わないからやめな！
If you're thinking of cooking Hayashi rice right now, don't! You won't make it in time!

24
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:01,000
絶対間に合わないから！
There's absolutely no way you'll make it!

25
00:04:01,500 --> 00:04:06,000
まあね、何か食べたり飲んだりしながら、ぜひね、ゆっくり楽しんでもらえると嬉しいです！
Well, grab something to eat or drink, and I hope you can sit back and enjoy!

26
00:04:07,500 --> 00:04:10,500
それでは、もうそろそろ始まるので、
It's about to start, so...

27
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:13,200
今しばらくお待ちください！
...please wait just a little longer!

28
00:04:13,200 --> 00:04:16,000
最後まで見てねー！
Watch until the very end, okay!

29
00:05:02,548 --> 00:05:07,548
風真いろは 生誕ライブ 2026 行くよー！
Kazama Iroha Birthday Live 2026, here we go!

30
00:05:11,648 --> 00:05:14,348
「いっせーのーで」で鳴り響いた
With an "un, deux, trois," resounded...

31
00:05:14,348 --> 00:05:17,048
スタートの合図
...the starting signal.

32
00:05:17,048 --> 00:05:19,848
なぞった線で結んだ世界
The world bound by traced lines...

33
00:05:19,848 --> 00:05:25,248
色づけていく ここから
...begins to color from here.

34
00:05:33,248 --> 00:05:38,048
物心がつく頃 すでにここにあった
By the time I understood, it was already here...

35
00:05:38,048 --> 00:05:41,048
僕じゃない誰かの記憶は
...the memory of someone else, not me,

36
00:05:41,048 --> 00:05:44,248
夕日と共に蘇る
returns along with the setting sun.

37
00:05:44,248 --> 00:05:49,048
古ぼけた絵本を取り出して
Taking out a worn-out picture book,

38
00:05:49,048 --> 00:05:54,048
落書きの中に一つの答えを見つけた
I found a single answer within the scribbles.

39
00:05:54,048 --> 00:05:57,248
自分の価値に目を疑って
Doubting my own worth,

40
00:05:57,248 --> 00:06:00,048
どこまでだって落ちていけるの
how far down can I possibly fall?

41
00:06:00,048 --> 00:06:02,548
どこか遠くに消えてしまいたい
I want to disappear somewhere far away.

42
00:06:02,548 --> 00:06:05,448
こんな世界じゃ僕は要らない
In a world like this, I'm not needed.

43
00:06:05,448 --> 00:06:10,548
カウントダウンは始まっているよ
The countdown has already begun.

44
00:06:10,548 --> 00:06:13,248
「いっせーのーで」で声を上げて
With an "un, deux, trois," raise your voice,

45
00:06:13,248 --> 00:06:15,848
聞こえてくるんだ
and it will be heard.

46
00:06:15,848 --> 00:06:18,448
自分の影 of 長さに気づく
Noticing the length of my own shadow...

47
00:06:18,448 --> 00:06:21,048
もうこんな時間だ
"It's already that time."

48
00:06:21,048 --> 00:06:23,848
一等星が顔を出した
The brightest star has shown its face.

49
00:06:23,848 --> 00:06:26,548
届きそうで手を伸ばした
Reaching out my hand as if I could grasp it.

50
00:06:26,548 --> 00:06:29,248
次は僕についてきなよ
"Next, follow after me,"

51
00:06:29,248 --> 00:06:32,048
どんな暗闇でも
"no matter how deep the darkness."

52
00:06:32,048 --> 00:06:34,248
もういいかい？ まだだよ
"Are you ready?" "Not yet."

53
00:06:34,248 --> 00:06:37,048
幕は上がりだした
The curtain has started to rise.

54
00:06:37,048 --> 00:06:39,548
もういいかい？ まだだよ
"Are you ready?" "Not yet."

55
00:06:39,548 --> 00:06:44,248
色づけていく ここから
Coloring begins from here.

56
00:06:53,048 --> 00:06:55,848
10年後の僕らは
Ten years from now, we...

57
00:06:55,848 --> 00:06:58,548
すれ違いばかりで
...will only be passing each other by.

58
00:06:58,548 --> 00:07:01,248
幻想に想いを馳せては
As we lose ourselves in illusions...

59
00:07:01,248 --> 00:07:04,248
「戻れない」そう思い込んだ
...convinced that "we can never go back."

60
00:07:04,248 --> 00:07:09,048
くたびれた心に追い打ちを
Striking another blow to an already tired heart,

61
00:07:09,048 --> 00:07:12,048
あの頃と変わらない夕日も
even the sunset, unchanged since those days,,

62
00:07:12,048 --> 00:07:14,548
なんとも思わない
doesn't make me feel anything anymore.

63
00:07:14,548 --> 00:07:17,548
自分を信じ歩いていければ
If I can believe in myself and keep walking,

64
00:07:17,548 --> 00:07:20,048
どこまでだって登れるのにな
I could have climbed to any height.

65
00:07:20,048 --> 00:07:22,548
カットをまたぐその空白に
In the blank space spanning between cuts,

66
00:07:22,548 --> 00:07:25,248
大切なもの見落としている
I am overlooking what's truly important.

67
00:07:25,248 --> 00:07:30,848
見つけられないと泣き喚く君へ
To you, crying out because you can't find it.

68
00:07:30,848 --> 00:07:33,248
「いっせーのーで」で声を上げて
With an "un, deux, trois," raise your voice,

69
00:07:33,248 --> 00:07:35,848
聞こえてくるんだ
and it will be heard.

70
00:07:35,848 --> 00:07:38,248
自分の影の長さに気づく
Noticing the length of my own shadow...

71
00:07:38,248 --> 00:07:41,048
もうこんな時間だ
"It's already that time."

72
00:07:41,048 --> 00:07:43,848
一等星で駆け抜ける君
You, running past like the brightest star,

73
00:07:43,848 --> 00:07:46,548
くっついていただけの僕でも
even for someone like me who just tagged along,

74
00:07:46,548 --> 00:07:49,248
君の前を走れるからな
I can run ahead of you.

75
00:07:49,248 --> 00:07:53,048
こんな頼りない僕でも
Even for someone as unreliable as me.

76
00:08:13,248 --> 00:08:18,548
宝箱はホコリをかぶったまま無くした
The treasure chest was lost, covered in dust.

77
00:08:18,548 --> 00:08:23,848
鍵はずっと君のポケットの中にあった
The key was in your pocket all along.

78
00:08:23,848 --> 00:08:29,248
散らばっていた全てが今一つに重なる
Everything that was scattered is now overlapping as one.

79
00:08:29,248 --> 00:08:34,248
手を取り始めよう 僕たちの物語
Let's take each other's hands and begin our story.

80
00:08:34,248 --> 00:08:39,548
一度は要らないと思った
Though I once thought I didn't need it,

81
00:08:39,548 --> 00:08:47,548
今なら胸を張れる気がしたんだ
I feel like I can hold my head high now.

82
00:08:47,548 --> 00:08:52,548
愛おしくて
So dear to me.

83
00:08:52,548 --> 00:08:55,848
掛け声はいつも
Our rallying cry is always...

84
00:08:55,848 --> 00:08:58,848
「いっせーのーで」で声を上げて
...with an "un, deux, trois," raise your voice!

85
00:08:58,848 --> 00:09:01,548
「いっせーのーで」で声を上げて
With an "un, deux, trois," raise your voice,

86
00:09:01,548 --> 00:09:03,848
聞こえてくるんだ
and it will be heard.

87
00:09:03,848 --> 00:09:06,248
自分の影の長さに気づく
Noticing the length of my own shadow...

88
00:09:06,248 --> 00:09:09,048
もうこんな時間だ
"It's already that time."

89
00:09:09,048 --> 00:09:11,848
一等星が顔を出した
The brightest star has shown its face.

90
00:09:11,848 --> 00:09:14,548
届きそうで手を伸ばした
Reaching out my hand as if I could grasp it.

91
00:09:14,548 --> 00:09:17,248
次は僕についてきなよ
"Next, follow after me,"

92
00:09:17,248 --> 00:09:20,048
どんな暗闇でも
"no matter how deep the darkness."

93
00:09:20,048 --> 00:09:22,248
もういいかい？ まだだよ
"Are you ready?" "Not yet."

94
00:09:22,248 --> 00:09:25,048
泣きじゃくった声で
With a sobbing voice,

95
00:09:25,048 --> 00:09:27,548
もういいかい？ まだだよ
"Are you ready?" "Not yet."

96
00:09:27,548 --> 00:09:30,248
笑う君が見えた
I saw you smiling.

97
00:09:30,248 --> 00:09:32,848
もういいかい？ まだだよ
"Are you ready?" "Not yet."

98
00:09:32,848 --> 00:09:36,248
幕は上がりだした
The curtain has started to rise.

99
00:09:36,248 --> 00:09:38,248
もういいかい？ もういいよ
"Are you ready?" "Yes, I am!"

100
00:09:38,248 --> 00:09:44,048
色づけていく ここから
Coloring begins from here.

101
00:10:15,123 --> 00:10:17,323
はい！というわけで
Alright, everyone!

102
00:10:17,323 --> 00:10:19,823
始まりましたー！
It has finally begun!

103
00:10:21,023 --> 00:10:23,923
風真いろは生誕ライブ2026
Kazama Iroha Birthday Live 2026...

104
00:10:23,923 --> 00:10:26,523
スタート！
...starts now!

105
00:10:26,523 --> 00:10:32,023
みんな、こんばんはー！見えてる？
Good evening, everyone! Can you see me?

106
00:10:34,023 --> 00:10:36,523
はい、ということで本日のハッシュタグはこちら！
Alright, and here is today's hashtag!

107
00:10:36,523 --> 00:10:42,523
こちらね、みんな、いっぱいポストしていっぱいカッコいいとこ撮ってくださいね。頼むよ！
Please use this hashtag, post a lot, and take tons of cool screenshots of me. I'm counting on you!

108
00:10:43,023 --> 00:10:47,023
この風真いろはがイケメンであることを世の中に知らしめられるのは、
The only ones who can let the world know...

109
00:10:47,023 --> 00:10:51,023
お前たちだけ、お前たちだけなので、よろしくお願いします！
...how cool Kazama Iroha is are you guys, so I'm counting on you!

110
00:10:52,023 --> 00:10:54,823
はい、そして今回のライブ、タイトルがついております。
Also, this concert has a title.

111
00:10:55,223 --> 00:10:58,823
「Wind Trails」というタイトルがついておりますが、
It's titled "Wind Trails."

112
00:11:01,023 --> 00:11:04,223
そのまま訳して結構お気づきの方も多かったんですが、
Many of you probably figured out the literal translation,

113
00:11:04,223 --> 00:11:09,423
風の軌跡という、あの、意味を込めて付けさせていただき、
but it carries the meaning of "trail of the wind."

114
00:11:09,423 --> 00:11:13,223
今回ライブ、いろいろ頑張って、考えさせていただきました。
I put a lot of hard work and thought into planning this concert.

115
00:11:13,223 --> 00:11:16,023
なのでね、最後まで楽しんでもらえると嬉しいです。
So, I hope you enjoy it until the very end.

116
00:11:16,523 --> 00:11:23,523
そして1曲目ね、「かくれんぼ」、歌わせていただきました！どうだったかなー？
And for the first song, I sang "Kakurenbo"! How did you like it?

117
00:11:25,023 --> 00:11:28,023
そして、今日、室内ライブだと思ったでしょ？
Also, you thought this was an indoor concert today, right?

118
00:11:28,823 --> 00:11:30,023
見て！
Take a look!

119
00:11:31,023 --> 00:11:37,023
曲中にドームが開きましたー！イェーイ！すごい！
The dome opened during the song! Yay! That was amazing!

120
00:11:38,823 --> 00:11:42,423
やっぱりね、なかなか現地ライブって、できてもさ、青空の下で
Real-life concerts don't often give us the chance...

121
00:11:42,423 --> 00:11:45,323
なかなか歌ってることがないので、
...to sing beneath the open blue sky.

122
00:11:46,023 --> 00:11:52,023
いつか俺たちとお前たちの次元が交わって、空の下で歌えるような世界が
Maybe one day our dimensions will cross, and a world where we can sing together under the sky...

123
00:11:52,023 --> 00:11:56,023
来るかもしれないけど、やってみたくてね。今回は、
...will come, but I really wanted to try it, so this time,

124
00:11:56,023 --> 00:12:00,023
空の下で歌うっていうこの演出をやらせていただきましたー！
I wanted to perform this staging where I sing under the sky!

125
00:12:00,023 --> 00:12:02,023
めっちゃいいでしょ？
Isn't it so great?

126
00:12:02,023 --> 00:12:05,023
ステージもめっちゃかっこいいんで、
The stage is also super cool,

127
00:12:05,023 --> 00:12:08,523
今日はね、たぶんいっぱい見る機会あると思いますが、
so you'll have plenty of chances to see it today.

128
00:12:08,523 --> 00:12:13,023
ゆっくり隅から隅まで。アーカイブ勢もきっといると思うんで、
Take your time looking at every corner. I'm sure the archive-watchers will too,

129
00:12:13,023 --> 00:12:16,523
本当にいろんな細部こだわってるんで、細かく見てくださいね。
because we really paid attention to every detail, so look closely!

130
00:12:17,023 --> 00:12:19,423
ということで、
Anyway...

131
00:12:19,423 --> 00:12:21,523
お水飲んでいいですかね？
Can I drink some water?

132
00:12:21,523 --> 00:12:24,023
お水を、お、うっ、やめろ！
Let me get some water... Whoa, wait, stop!

133
00:12:24,023 --> 00:12:27,523
俺の頭をいじ...うっ、やめっ
Don't touch my head... Ugh, stop that-

134
00:12:30,023 --> 00:12:34,023
頭をいじくり回されて、ヘッドセットになりました。
They messed with my head, and now I'm using a headset.

135
00:12:34,023 --> 00:12:38,023
そして、水が、お水、用意してくれたんだよね。
And they prepared some water for me.

136
00:12:38,023 --> 00:12:41,023
みんなに見える水！
Water that all of you can actually see!

137
00:12:42,523 --> 00:12:43,823
うまい！
So good!

138
00:12:43,823 --> 00:12:50,023
うますぎる！この、この振りはちょっと怒られそうだからもうできないけど、うますぎる！
Too delicious! I might get scolded if I do this pose again, but it's so good!

139
00:12:50,523 --> 00:12:52,223
うまいなー。
Ah, that hits the spot.

140
00:12:52,223 --> 00:12:55,223
これで、あと1時間やるか？そういうわけにはいかないんで、
Should I just do this for another hour? I can't do that,

141
00:12:55,223 --> 00:12:57,023
一回ちょっと返して...
so let me put this away...

142
00:12:59,023 --> 00:13:00,023
それじゃあ、
Well then,

143
00:13:00,023 --> 00:13:04,223
水分補給もさせてもらって、息も整ったんじゃない？
now that I've hydrated and caught my breath,

144
00:13:05,023 --> 00:13:08,523
はい、次の曲、早速やっていきたいと思います！
I'd like to get right into the next song!

145
00:13:09,023 --> 00:13:11,523
それでは次の曲、聴いてください。
Now, please listen to the next song.

146
00:13:11,523 --> 00:13:13,223
「白線」
"Hakusen"

147
00:13:16,823 --> 00:13:19,223
澄み渡った空に白線
A white line in the clear blue sky...

148
00:13:19,223 --> 00:13:24,023
あの地平を超えて
...beyond that horizon!

149
00:13:24,523 --> 00:13:29,823
はい！はい！はい！はい！もっと！はい！はい！
Yes! Yes! Yes! Yes! More! Yes! Yes!

150
00:13:35,023 --> 00:13:40,023
始まりはちょっと軽い期待で その欠片そっとポケットしまって
It started with light expectations, tucking those pieces gently into my pocket

151
00:13:40,023 --> 00:13:45,323
屋上 遠い空の向こうを見てた
On the rooftop, looking beyond the distant sky

152
00:13:45,323 --> 00:13:51,023
この足でどこに行けるかなって わかってないけどわかってるんだ
Wondering where these feet can take me, I don't know, but yet I do

153
00:13:51,023 --> 00:13:55,323
白昼 淡い月に手を伸ばした
Reaching my hand out to the pale moon in broad daylight

154
00:13:55,323 --> 00:14:01,023
掠れたエコー でも答えはもう 初めからちゃんと持っていたんだよ
A faded echo, but I already had the answer right from the start

155
00:14:01,023 --> 00:14:03,523
メイビー この想いは
Maybe this feeling...

156
00:14:04,023 --> 00:14:07,023
メイビー この想いは
Maybe this feeling...

157
00:14:07,023 --> 00:14:09,523
マスビー 熱を増して
Must be, heating up...

158
00:14:10,023 --> 00:14:12,023
マスビー 熱を増して
Must be, heating up...

159
00:14:12,023 --> 00:14:14,223
ほらね、飛べるんだ
See? I can fly!

160
00:14:14,223 --> 00:14:19,523
もっと高く 高く 高くまで 羽ばたいてみたい
I want to flap my wings and go higher, higher, even higher

161
00:14:19,823 --> 00:14:25,023
今日に未来色の軌道描いて 地平の先まで
Drawing a future-colored trail in today, all the way to the horizon

162
00:14:25,023 --> 00:14:30,023
届かない歌はない 迷いはもうない
There is no song that won't reach, I have no doubts anymore

163
00:14:30,023 --> 00:14:35,523
どんな世界も瞬間も揺るがない 愛が在るから
Unwavering in any world, at any moment, because love exists

164
00:14:36,023 --> 00:14:38,823
澄み渡った空に白線
A white line in the clear blue sky

165
00:14:38,823 --> 00:14:41,223
不安と期待とアンビバレント
Anxiety, expectation, and ambivalence

166
00:14:41,223 --> 00:14:43,623
でも声はもう気づいてる
But my voice has already realized

167
00:14:43,623 --> 00:14:46,823
もっと高く 高く 高く 飛んでいける！
I can fly higher, higher, and higher!

168
00:14:57,023 --> 00:15:01,023
途切れ途切れの一縷でも
Even if it's just a broken thread...

169
00:15:00,071 --> 00:15:02,171
紡いでたら「一途」に変ったよ
When I spun them together, they turned into devotion.

170
00:15:02,171 --> 00:15:04,571
あたりさわりない言葉じゃ
With harmless, safe words,

171
00:15:04,571 --> 00:15:08,071
覆いきれないほどのマイワールド
I can't fully cover my own world.

172
00:15:08,071 --> 00:15:10,571
明日で呼ぶ声の持ち主は
The owner of the voice calling in tomorrow...

173
00:15:10,571 --> 00:15:13,271
他でもないこの心だった
...was none other than this heart of mine.

174
00:15:13,271 --> 00:15:15,571
見えないって言っている その言葉も
Even those words saying "I can't see"

175
00:15:15,571 --> 00:15:18,071
「言葉」だと足りないだけ
are just not enough as mere "words."

176
00:15:18,071 --> 00:15:20,071
掴んだもの 落としたもの
The things I grabbed, the things I dropped,

177
00:15:20,071 --> 00:15:24,071
転んだって立って見えた視界から
from the scenery I saw as I fell and stood up again,

178
00:15:24,071 --> 00:15:26,571
ロックユー！解き放って
Rock you! Release it!

179
00:15:26,571 --> 00:15:29,371
ロックユー！解き放って
Rock you! Release it!

180
00:15:29,371 --> 00:15:32,071
フォーユー！響きだして
For you! Start echoing!

181
00:15:32,071 --> 00:15:34,571
フォーユー！響きだして
For you! Start echoing!

182
00:15:34,571 --> 00:15:37,071
景色変えてゆく
The scenery is changing.

183
00:15:37,071 --> 00:15:42,271
まだ遠く遠くまで広がった空に
To the sky that stretches far, far away,

184
00:15:42,271 --> 00:15:47,571
やっと踏み出すこの一歩なんてちっぽけだけど
this first step I'm finally taking is tiny, but...

185
00:15:47,571 --> 00:15:52,571
届かない場所へと続いていく保存
...it continues towards an unreachable place.

186
00:15:52,571 --> 00:15:55,571
どんな風に雨に消えない
No matter the wind or rain, it won't fade...

187
00:15:55,571 --> 00:15:58,071
白線を描く
...as I draw a white line.

188
00:15:58,071 --> 00:16:03,571
もっと高く高くまで羽ばたいていたい
I want to flap my wings higher and higher.

189
00:16:03,571 --> 00:16:06,071
そして彼方色で繋ぐ
And connecting with yonder colors...

190
00:16:06,071 --> 00:16:08,571
地平で待ってて
...wait for me at the horizon.

191
00:16:08,571 --> 00:16:11,371
もう願いに嘘はない
There are no more lies in my wishes.

192
00:16:11,371 --> 00:16:13,871
ここが好き！
I love it here!

193
00:16:13,871 --> 00:16:16,871
どんな世界も瞬間も輝く
Every world and every moment shines...

194
00:16:16,871 --> 00:16:19,371
アイが在るから
...because love is there.

195
00:16:19,371 --> 00:16:21,871
今はただ想うこと言えばいい
Now, I just need to say what I feel:

196
00:16:21,871 --> 00:16:25,571
「愛しているよ！」
"I love you!"

197
00:16:35,471 --> 00:16:38,071
澄み渡った空に白線
A white line in the clear sky,

198
00:16:38,071 --> 00:16:40,871
不安と期待がアンビバレント
anxiety and expectation are ambivalent.

199
00:16:40,871 --> 00:16:43,371
でも「君」はもう気づいてる保存
But "you" already noticed.

200
00:16:43,371 --> 00:16:47,071
もっと高く高く高く飛んでいける
I can fly higher, higher, and higher!

201
00:17:01,071 --> 00:17:06,071
もっと
More...

202
00:17:06,071 --> 00:17:11,571
もっと
More...

203
00:17:11,571 --> 00:17:17,071
もっと
More...

204
00:17:17,071 --> 00:17:22,571
もっと
More...

205
00:17:22,571 --> 00:17:25,571
鏡よ 教えて
Mirror, mirror, tell me,

206
00:17:25,571 --> 00:17:30,071
私の証はどこにあるのだろう
where is my proof of existence?

207
00:17:30,071 --> 00:17:33,571
わからない わからないよ
I don't know, I don't know.

208
00:17:33,571 --> 00:17:36,571
周りと比べたってさ
Even if I compare myself to others,

209
00:17:36,571 --> 00:17:39,071
虚しくなるだけ
it only makes me feel empty.

210
00:17:39,071 --> 00:17:41,571
あのノイズが
That noise...

211
00:17:41,571 --> 00:17:44,271
海鳴りのように涙を奪う
...takes away my tears like the roaring of the sea.

212
00:17:44,271 --> 00:17:47,571
切り取った風景を保存
Taking the cut-out scenery,

213
00:17:47,571 --> 00:17:49,871
道標にしよう そうだ
let's make it our guidepost, yes.

214
00:17:49,871 --> 00:17:52,571
傷ついた感情も
If we can bring along...

215
00:17:52,571 --> 00:17:55,071
連れて行けたら
...even our hurt feelings...

216
00:17:55,071 --> 00:17:57,371
そっと響くカンパネラ
The Campanella gently echoes,

217
00:17:57,371 --> 00:18:00,271
新しい未来を感じてる
I'm feeling a new future.

218
00:18:00,271 --> 00:18:04,571
怖くたって進むしかないでしょう保存
Even if we are scared, we have to move forward, right?

219
00:18:04,571 --> 00:18:07,571
遠くまで
To the far distance...

220
00:18:07,571 --> 00:18:09,371
もっと もっと
More, more...

221
00:18:09,371 --> 00:18:11,871
届けこの祈りよ光となれ
Let this prayer reach, become the light!

222
00:18:11,871 --> 00:18:13,271
もっと もっと
More, more...

223
00:18:13,271 --> 00:18:15,571
少しずつでもいい
Even if it's little by little,

224
00:18:15,571 --> 00:18:18,571
私という答えを
the answer that is myself...

225
00:18:18,571 --> 00:18:21,071
もっと
More...

226
00:18:21,071 --> 00:18:26,571
もっと
More...

227
00:18:29,571 --> 00:18:32,571
夜空よ 教えて
Night sky, tell me,

228
00:18:32,571 --> 00:18:37,071
私の証は輝けるのかな
can my proof of existence shine?

229
00:18:37,071 --> 00:18:40,571
見つけたい 見つけたいよ
I want to find it, I want to find it.

230
00:18:40,571 --> 00:18:43,571
誰かの決めたレベルは
The levels set by others

231
00:18:43,571 --> 00:18:46,071
苦しくなるだけ
only make me suffer.

232
00:18:46,071 --> 00:18:48,571
ノイズも力に
I will turn even the noise...

233
00:18:48,571 --> 00:18:51,271
変えるよ 心に誓う
...into strength, I swear to my heart.

234
00:18:51,271 --> 00:18:54,071
錆びついた運命の保存
Let's turn...

235
00:18:54,071 --> 00:18:56,571
歯車を回そう ほら
...the rusted gears of fate, look!

236
00:18:56,571 --> 00:18:59,071
着飾った感情は
Because I will cast aside...

237
00:18:59,071 --> 00:19:02,071
脱ぎ捨てるから
...my dressed-up emotions.

238
00:19:02,071 --> 00:19:04,271
そっと紡ぐシンフォニア
The symphonia gently spun,

239
00:19:04,271 --> 00:19:07,071
叶えたい願いを信じてる保存
I believe in the wishes I want to grant.

240
00:19:07,071 --> 00:19:09,571
胸を張って歌うしかないでしょう
We just have to sing with our heads held high,

241
00:19:09,571 --> 00:19:11,271
全力で
with all our might!

242
00:19:11,271 --> 00:19:12,871
もっと もっと
More, more...

243
00:19:12,871 --> 00:19:18,071
やがて希望の歌に変わる日まで
Until the day it finally turns into a song of hope.

244
00:19:18,071 --> 00:19:20,571
もっと もっと
More, more...

245
00:19:20,571 --> 00:19:23,071
悩みながらでいい
It's fine to worry as we go,

246
00:19:23,071 --> 00:19:25,571
全てが宝物
everything is a treasure.

247
00:19:33,271 --> 00:19:36,071
いつの日かこの声を
If one day, this voice...痕跡が残る保存

248
00:19:36,071 --> 00:19:39,071
受け取ってくれたなら
...is received by you,

249
00:19:39,071 --> 00:19:41,571
この言葉を君に保存
I give these words to you:

250
00:19:41,571 --> 00:19:45,071
もう大丈夫 一人じゃない
"It's alright now, you are not alone."

251
00:19:45,071 --> 00:19:48,071
強い想いを
These strong feelings...

252
00:19:48,071 --> 00:19:51,071
繋ぐよ
...I will connect them.

253
00:19:51,071 --> 00:19:53,571
一歩踏み出してみた
I tried taking a step forward,

254
00:19:53,571 --> 00:19:56,571
優しく世界は微笑む保存
and the world gently smiles.

255
00:19:56,571 --> 00:19:58,571
高鳴る気持ちに身を任せて
Surrendering to this rising excitement,

256
00:19:58,571 --> 00:20:00,071
さあ行こう
let's go!

257
00:20:00,046 --> 00:20:01,146
...カンパネラ
...the Campanella.

258
00:20:01,146 --> 00:20:04,146
新しい未来を感じてる
I can feel the new future.

259
00:20:04,146 --> 00:20:09,146
怖くたって進むしかないでしょう
Even if I'm scared, I have no choice but to move forward, right?

260
00:20:09,146 --> 00:20:11,846
遠くまで
To somewhere far away...

261
00:20:11,846 --> 00:20:15,546
届けこの祈りよ 光となれ
Reach out, my prayer! Become the light.

262
00:20:15,546 --> 00:20:18,546
もっと もっと
More and more...

263
00:20:18,546 --> 00:20:22,546
少しずつでもいい「私」という答えを
Even if it's little by little, the answer called "myself"...

264
00:20:22,546 --> 00:20:30,946
もっと... もっと... もっと...
More... and more... and more...

265
00:21:07,546 --> 00:21:12,546
雨とペトラ
[Title: Rain and Petra]

266
00:21:26,446 --> 00:21:28,546
誰かが言った
Someone once said...

267
00:21:28,546 --> 00:21:31,946
いつか空は灰になって落ちるって
...that someday the sky will turn to ash and fall.

268
00:21:32,446 --> 00:21:36,146
妄想の世の中で日々を喰らっている
I'm devouring my days in a world of delusions.

269
00:21:36,546 --> 00:21:39,146
境界線を引いてしまうのも
Drawing a boundary line...

270
00:21:39,146 --> 00:21:41,846
今日、感覚のせいにして
...blaming it on my senses today.

271
00:21:42,146 --> 00:21:46,446
街の灯の海で居場所を探している
I'm searching for where I belong in a sea of city lights.

272
00:21:47,146 --> 00:21:49,546
どこへ行くにも
No matter where I go,

273
00:21:49,546 --> 00:21:52,246
この足は
these feet of mine...

274
00:21:52,246 --> 00:21:56,146
退屈に染まって動かない
...are stained with boredom and won't move.

275
00:21:56,846 --> 00:22:00,346
少しだけ先の
Even though all I want to see...

276
00:22:00,346 --> 00:22:04,646
景色が見たいだけなのにな
...is just a little bit of the scenery ahead.

277
00:22:06,046 --> 00:22:09,146
雨が降ったら 雨が降ったら きっと
When the rain falls, when the rain falls, surely...

278
00:22:09,146 --> 00:22:11,346
頬を濡らしてしまう
...it will wet my cheeks.

279
00:22:11,346 --> 00:22:13,646
枯れてしまった色ですら
Even the withered colors...

280
00:22:13,646 --> 00:22:15,946
愛しくなるのに
...become dear to me.

281
00:22:16,246 --> 00:22:19,346
目を瞑ったら 目を瞑ったら もっと
If I close my eyes, if I close my eyes, even more...

282
00:22:19,346 --> 00:22:21,546
遠く霞んでしまう
...they will grow hazy in the distance.

283
00:22:21,546 --> 00:22:23,746
煩くなった雨の音
The sound of the rain has become noisy.

284
00:22:23,746 --> 00:22:26,146
笑い飛ばしてくれ
Laugh it away for me!

285
00:22:35,346 --> 00:22:37,346
誰かが言った
Someone once said...

286
00:22:37,346 --> 00:22:40,846
いつか溜息は夜に化けて歌を歌う
...that someday, our sighs will turn into night and sing.

287
00:22:41,246 --> 00:22:45,046
妄想の世の中で日々を喰らっている
We're devouring the days within a world of delusion.

288
00:22:45,946 --> 00:22:48,346
優しい嘘を
Because we retraced...

289
00:22:48,346 --> 00:22:51,046
なぞったせいで
...those gentle lies...

290
00:22:51,046 --> 00:22:55,246
離れる声に気付かない
...I didn't notice the fading voice.

291
00:22:55,646 --> 00:22:58,146
溶けた月が
The melted moon...

292
00:22:58,146 --> 00:23:00,646
足元に落ちて
...fell at my feet...

293
00:23:00,646 --> 00:23:04,946
静かに揺れていた
...and quietly shimmered.

294
00:23:04,946 --> 00:23:08,046
夜が降ったら 夜が降ったら きっと
When the night falls, when the night falls, surely...

295
00:23:08,046 --> 00:23:10,246
今日を責めてしまう
...it will blame today.

296
00:23:10,246 --> 00:23:12,546
満たされない日々の底で
At the bottom of these unfulfilled days...

297
00:23:12,546 --> 00:23:14,846
夢を見ているだけ
...I'm simply dreaming.

298
00:23:15,146 --> 00:23:18,246
目を逸らしても 目を逸らしても ずっと
Even if I look away, even if I look away, forever...

299
00:23:18,246 --> 00:23:20,446
後悔と哀の隙間
...in the gap between regret and sorrow...

300
00:23:20,446 --> 00:23:22,546
取り残されてしまう前に
...before I get left behind...

301
00:23:22,546 --> 00:23:25,046
手を伸ばしてくれ
...give me your hand!

302
00:23:34,446 --> 00:23:37,346
雨が降ったら 雨が降ったら きっと
When the rain falls, when the rain falls, surely...

303
00:23:39,446 --> 00:23:43,746
雨が降ったら 雨が降ったら きっと
When the rain falls, when the rain falls, surely...

304
00:23:44,246 --> 00:23:47,346
湿るアスファルトを背に映して俯いた
I hung my head, with the damp asphalt reflected on my back.

305
00:23:49,146 --> 00:23:51,346
独りぼっちで
All by myself,

306
00:23:51,346 --> 00:23:53,946
また明日に期待をして
I place my hopes in tomorrow once again.

307
00:23:54,046 --> 00:23:57,146
雨が降ったら 雨が降ったら きっと
When the rain falls, when the rain falls, surely...

308
00:23:57,146 --> 00:23:59,346
頬を濡らしてしまう
...it will wet my cheeks.

309
00:23:59,346 --> 00:24:01,646
枯れてしまった色ですら
Even the withered colors...

310
00:24:01,646 --> 00:24:03,946
愛しくなるのに
...become dear to me.

311
00:24:04,246 --> 00:24:07,346
目を瞑ったら 目を瞑ったら もっと
If I close my eyes, if I close my eyes, even more...

312
00:24:07,346 --> 00:24:09,546
遠く霞んでしまう
...they will grow hazy in the distance.

313
00:24:09,546 --> 00:24:11,746
煩くなった雨の音
The sound of the rain has become noisy.

314
00:24:11,746 --> 00:24:14,346
笑い飛ばしてくれ
Laugh it away for me!

315
00:24:46,046 --> 00:24:51,046
群青讃歌
[Title: Ultramarine Anthem]

316
00:25:08,094 --> 00:25:10,994
繋がっていたいって信じられる言葉
The words that let me believe we want to stay connected

317
00:25:10,994 --> 00:25:13,994
だってもう昨日の僕らにおさらば
Because we've already said goodbye to the us of yesterday

318
00:25:14,094 --> 00:25:16,894
青い春を過ごした
We spent our blue youth

319
00:25:16,894 --> 00:25:19,494
遠い稲妻
with a distant lightning strike

320
00:25:19,694 --> 00:25:22,394
そっと泣いて 前だけを向けたら
If I could just weep softly and look forward,

321
00:25:22,494 --> 00:25:25,594
きっとどんなに楽になれていたろうな
how much easier it would have surely been

322
00:25:25,694 --> 00:25:28,094
この心を揺らした
That single thread of hope

323
00:25:28,094 --> 00:25:30,994
一縷の望みは
which shook my heart

324
00:25:31,094 --> 00:25:36,094
ないものねだりは辞めた 未完成人間
I've stopped wishing for the impossible, incomplete human

325
00:25:36,094 --> 00:25:41,594
素晴らしい世界だけが 答えを握ってる
Only this wonderful world holds the answer

326
00:25:45,094 --> 00:25:47,094
諦めてしまうほど
So much that you might give up,

327
00:25:47,094 --> 00:25:49,094
この先たくさんの
there are many

328
00:25:49,094 --> 00:25:51,394
後悔が君を待ってるけど
regrets waiting for you ahead, but...

329
00:25:51,394 --> 00:25:53,694
もうない 迷いはしないよ
No more, I won't hesitate anymore

330
00:25:53,694 --> 00:25:56,594
この傷も愛しく思えてしまうほど
To the point that even these wounds feel precious

331
00:25:56,594 --> 00:25:58,294
重ねてしまうよ
I'll keep piling them on

332
00:25:58,294 --> 00:26:02,094
不格好なまんまでいいから
Because it's fine to be clumsy

333
00:26:02,594 --> 00:26:05,494
走れ その歩幅で
Run, at your own pace

334
00:26:05,494 --> 00:26:08,094
走れ 声轟かせてくれ
Run, let your voice roar

335
00:26:08,094 --> 00:26:10,894
期待と不安を同じくらい抱きしめて
Embracing both expectations and anxiety in equal measure

336
00:26:10,894 --> 00:26:18,094
君と今を紡ぐ未来照らして
Illuminate the future that weaves "now" with you

337
00:26:30,094 --> 00:26:33,094
顔も名前も知らない僕たちが
We, who don't know each other's faces or names,

338
00:26:33,094 --> 00:26:35,894
たった1つの音をかき鳴らす
